27. victorum nepotes, etc. ε the commander of the Pompeian army at Thapsus was Metellus Scipio, grandson of the Metellus Numidi- cus who commanded (109—107 Rc.) in the war against Jugurtha. The Pompeians who fell at Thap- sus, ten thousand in number, are here described as offerings at the tomb of the Numidian king. It is interesting to remember in this connection that Sallust had pub- lished his jugurtha in recent years.
